{
  "doc_id": "57892",
  "text": "This method allows the effect size of repeated measures in different treatment groups to be directly compared, as the effect size is not influenced by the treatment condition's effect on posttreatment SD [CITATION_1] . The effect size is coded such that positive values indicate lowering of the anxiety score. The independent group comparison between the treatment condition and control condition was calculated as the difference between the treatment and control effect sizes. Thresholds of effect size suggested by Cohen are 0.2, 0.5, and 0.8 for small, medium, and large effects, respectively [CITATION_2] . Variance was calculated according the generalized method described [CITATION_3] , as given in Equation 3.",
